  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to determine in high risk diabetics if the positive predictive value
      of stress echocardiography is superior to the positive predictive value of stress
      scintigraphy in the diagnosis of coronary stenosis &gt; 50%.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Comparison Between Stress Echocardiography and Stress Scintigraphy in the Detection of Silent
      Myocardial Ischemia
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
